  "key_findings": [
    "Gauss's Law (flux) and Electric Potential (fixed kq) share the 1n floor — div only.",
    "Electric Potential Energy with fixed charges also reaches 1n.",
    "Biot-Savart and Magnetic Dipole Field are the costliest at 12n (canonical); sin/cos add only 1n each as complex EML nodes.",
    "The 1/r² family (Coulomb, E-field) costs more than 1/r (potential, PE) due to the pow node.",
    "Energy equations (capacitor, inductor) are structurally identical at 7n canonical / 5n with constant folding.",
